13 AMENDMENT NO. 1. Strike the stricken title, enacting clause, and
entire bill and insert:
14
15 "An Act relating to construction by political
subdivisions; amending 61 O.S. 2021, Section 108,
16 which relates to written statements under oath to
accompany bids; and removing requirement for certain
17 statements to be disclosed under oath; and declaring
an emergency.
18
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
21 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 61 O.S. 2021, Section 108, is
22 amended to read as follows:
23 Section 108. Each bidder shall accompany the bid with a written
24 statement under oath disclosing the following information:
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 898 Page 1
1 1. The nature of any partnership, joint venture or other
2 business relationships then in effect or which existed within one
3 (1) year prior to the date of such statement with the architect,
4 engineer or other party to the project;
5 2. Any such business relationship then in effect or which
6 existed within one (1) year prior to the date of such statement
7 between any officer or director of the bidding company and any
8 officer or director of the architectural or engineering firm or
9 other party to the project; and
10 3. The names of all persons having any such business
11 relationships and the positions they hold with their respective
12 companies or firms. If none of the business relationships
13 hereinabove mentioned exist, then a statement to that effect.
14 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
15 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
16 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
17 be in full force from and after its passage and approval."
